    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-21T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="450"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/376: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-21T19:00:00-03:00"
                            >September 21, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. On learning on September 19 that Campinas had been bombarded by Federal
                    forces I verbally protested to Foreign Minister. On learning today of injury to
                    property of Bond and Share I again protested verbally. Minister recognizes
                    propriety of representation but states that aviation corps is uncontrolled and
                    irresponsible.</p>
                <p>Have requested urgent audience with Dr. <persName corresp="#p_VGD1">Getulio
                        Vargas</persName> to represent that the situation caused by bombardment of
                    an open town is already grave and will become’ more so if through bombardment
                    American lives are lost.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MEV1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
